    <stitle>VT 365 Diesel Engine - 2004 Model Year - ENGINE ELECTRICAL - Description of Engine Sensors and Valves -
        Engine Oil Pressure (EOP) Sensor
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s26510.2.6" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Engine Oil Pressure (EOP) Sensor</title>
        <figure id="f11" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figJ09/J09015.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>EOP sensor</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>The EOP sensor, a ceramic diaphragm sensor, detects engine oil pressure.</para>
        <para>The EOP signal is monitored by the ECM for operation of the instrument panel pressure gauge and optional
            EWPS.
        </para>
        <para>The EOP sensor is installed in the oil filter base.</para>
    </svcproc>
